# Common Anti-Patterns to Avoid

## Commit Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Mixing unrelated changes in one commit
- ❌ Committing broken code
- ❌ Vague commit messages
- ❌ Committing temporary files or logs

## Branch Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Long-lived feature branches
- ❌ Merging without cleanup
- ❌ Working directly on production branches
- ❌ Forgetting to delete merged branches

## Workflow Anti-Patterns
- ❌ Skipping code reviews in team environments
- ❌ Inconsistent commit message formats
- ❌ Not using semantic versioning
- ❌ Ignoring automated checks
